6. Kahn Algorithm
Definition

Kahn Algorithm is a BFS algorithm used to find Topological Sorting.

Idea

Process nodes having indegree = 0.

Because

No prerequisites.
7. Algorithm (5 Steps)
Step 1

Calculate indegree.

↓

Step 2

Push all indegree = 0 nodes into queue.

↓

Step 3

Pop node.

↓

Step 4

Decrease indegree of neighbors.

↓

Step 5

If neighbor becomes indegree = 0

Push into queue.

Repeat until queue becomes empty.

